gomodel:SYNGO_4653  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3. immunostaining and confocal microscopy; \"CaMKIIα (CAMK2A), α-actinin-1 (ACTN1), and Cdk5 and its activators colocalize in hippocampal neurons\"\n\nPotential postsynaptic localization, but in absence of high-resolution data we conservatively opt for \"synapse\" ontology for now.. Experimental description: \"Dissociated hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18 (E18) rat brains ...\"\n\nmonoclonal α-actinin-1 antibody (1:1000; Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO)" ;
